   ELECTRICAL ENGINEERING, AUTEEE},
Year = {2022},
Pages = {902-906},
Note = {5th International Conference on Automation Electronics and Electrical
   Engineering, Shenyang, PEOPLES R CHINA, NOV 18-20, 2022},
Abstract = {With the emergence of new technologies, new applications, and new
   business formats, new fraudulent methods emerge and continue to evolve
   and upgrade. Among them, the main platforms of online fraud are various
   fraudulent websites, and feature identification of fraudulent websites
   is a necessary way to effectively prevent such crimes. At present,
   common fraudulent website detection techniques are mainly based on the
   classification of known fraud types. This method can only find and known
   fraudulent types of fraudulent sites. There is no effective way to
   quickly spot new scam sites. To address this problem, we employ DAN
   transfer learning technology to timely discover fraudulent website. By
   studying the correlation between new fraudulent websites and known black
   sample websites, high-value Information is transferred from known models
   and data to new fraudulent sites that need to be learned, and new
   fraudulent sites can be quickly discovered. To verify the effectiveness
   of the method, we conducted a comparison experiment of multiple
   algorithms using 71,500 training data and 28,500 testing data. The
   results of comparison experiment show that the DAN method could identify
   new fraudulent websites with high accuracy.},
