Number = {3},
Pages = {124-131},
Abstract = {In the current scenario of Internet-enabled gadgets, most of the people
   are fully dependent on mobile phones and installed apps. The smartphone
   users keep their data and personal information on cloud services and
   access on their mobile phones via smartphone apps for the ease and 24 X
   7 availability of the information. But such scenarios are nowadays
   giving threats to personal data especially due to high risk of security
   issues arising from the installed in smartphone. Currently, everybody is
   using smartphone apps for their personal, official, or social networks.
   From the deep adavancements of security, this is reported that the
   research on mobile networks security is very challanging to secure the
   personal and high sentive data leakage. Android is one of the popular
   smartphone platforms that is used widely with a millions of apps. The
   presented research manuscript is implementing the machine learning
   algorithm for smartphone forensic with a specific scenario of Android
   Apps so that overall analytics with effectual security can be
   maintained. The experimetal work ensured outperformed forensic security
   and predictive analysis by using AAPT android application tool. The
   expected classes of Manifest Analysis for Malware(MAMA) dataset can be
   allocated for testing dataset with the same mathematical functions as
   performed by the previous classification model.},
