   (i-PACT), Vellore, INDIA, APR 21-22, 2017},
Abstract = {Facial expression is become a prominent way of understanding people. In
   past many decades many people have been attracted to this field of image
   processing as it helps in many of the real time application. Currently,
   there have been many applications which are based on human facial
   expression recognition. One of its application is controlling the music
   player on the basis of human emotions and moods. In this work a system
   is developed which can help in reducing the rate of crime caused due to
   anger. Here the focus will be to calculate the human emotions and
   transfer this data to the responsible organization which can take some
   instance step to avoid crime. The system process works in java. This
   application which is based on detecting human facial expressions will be
   used to operate an alert system that is very much needed to reduce the
   crime rate. It can reduce the crime rate worldwide by sending alerts to
   nearby police stations so that people won't become victim of any crime.
   This application is purely bases on detecting facial expression of
   people because it is easy to read the different kind of emotions on the
   human face. This data of expressions will be used to train a system so
   that this application can be used in a system to detect facial
   expressions.},
