Abstract = {The proliferation of social media and software, such as building
   information modelling (BIM), has led to an unprecedented accumulation of
   data in the last few years, which can be tracked, tagged and
   scanned.With it, buildings and cities have been transformed into portals
   for information. Andrew Hudson-Smith, Director at the Centre for
   Advanced Spatial Analysis, University College London (UCL), describes
