   Harmony, Limassol, CYPRUS, APR 13-14, 2018},
Organization = {Inst Sci Commun},
Abstract = {Purpose: The purpose of the article is to evaluate the systems of
   economic security of credit organizations and to increase their
   effectiveness by implementing new innovational methods in view of
   digitization of national economy. For this purpose, the situation with
   state interference with the work of banking system in modern conditions
   was analyzed, the level of digitization of the banking system in view of
   the current situation according to the Bank of Russia was studied, and
   dynamics of transformation of the indicators of economic security of the
   systems of financial establishments was tracked. Growth of popularity of
   Internet banking leads to the growth of the number of cyber attacks on
   web-sites of credit and financial establishment, so in order to reduce
   the risk of accounts hacking, the banks have to constantly update their
   security systems. Innovational tools of identification will allow
   recognizing specific customer and minimize the risks of unsanctioned
   access.
   Methodology: The research is performed with application of the methods
   of graphical presentation of information, neural network analysis, trend
   analysis, method of comparison, analogy, and systematization.
   Results: According to the peculiarities of formation of the model of
   information economy, we considered the main directions of development of
   cybercrimes and analyzed statistics and dynamics of fraud in Internet
   environment. The directions of increase of economic security of the
   system of Internet banking include implementation of the tools of neural
   network analysis. This mechanism will allow for precise and effective
   evaluation of the system of security of credit organization and for
   reduction of probability of assigning a password or access key. This
   indicative model of economic security of credit organization will allow
   saving bank's resources on production of electronic keys and passwords.
   Recommendations: the studied directions of the indicative model for
   increasing the security of Internet systems of credit organizations
   allow expanding the possibilities of remote banking services.
   Implementation of neural network analysis will allow for maximum
   reduction of the risk of unsanctioned access to customers' accounts. The
   directions of development of the systems of economic and information
   security of credit and payment operators could be used as methodological
   directions for further optimization of remote financial tools.},
